Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine brown. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Ink or pencil '12'. Name Eukleitos. Trimmed. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0350.15.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0940)
